body.description: Globe Electric Belmont Collection adds a quiet sophistication to any room. Its Black finish pairs cleverly with antique brass accents to evoke a luxurious yet industrial feel amongst all its onlookers and perfectly complements any space. The arched arm of the Belmont desk lamp makes this a truly standalone piece. Suitable for a home office, living room or entryway, this lamp delivers just the right amount of light. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just what we were looking for
reviews.reviewText: We have a new head board with new bedside tables and were looking for a lamp which was USB plug-in capable. I have been searching for "the" lamp since last year. Either prices were too high, reviews were terrible or a number of other issues.The negative reviews on here didn't really relate to the lamp, so those were discarded as null to me. I went on other websites that sell this same lamp, and for the most, they were all positive. In addition, other sites were typically double the price found on Amazon.So it made it past the review stage and of course the looks stage. Thus I purchased it.All parts were within the box and were still wrapped in the plastic that covered each of the pieces. The exterior of one box was damaged, but fortunately it didn't affect the lamp within.The only thing you have to do, once unwrapped, is find a lightbulb (40W or less) and twist it and the shade into place. Then tada! You are done.I did have one issue with the lightbulb not working. It worked, and then it wouldn't turn on. I was able to fix that by finding another bulb. So far both lights are working well and add a great ambiance to the room.So at this point I have absolutely no regrets in purchasing it. It's stable enough that my cat will not be able to knock it off with their typical "let's knock everything off the table". It's sturdy and puts out a good amount of light. And the price is right!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 1, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very nice desk lamps
reviews.reviewText: We got these lamps for our bedside lamps. They look great, and work well. I really like the switch on the base, rather than the cord so you dont have to go digging for the switch.I havent used the USB ports yet, but they're a nice feature too.The only downside I have has they are made to be desk lamps, not nightstand lamps, and as such, they are made direct all the light onto something, like say, a desk! It doesnt light the room overall, which I guess I expected. So I'll likely see if I can track down a clear shade for these. But of course, that isnt the lamp's fault.All in all though, I really like these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 7, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Mad Men looking lamp
reviews.reviewText: I really liked this lamp - it is very sleek and polished and has a classic Mid Century look to it. Very Don Draper/Mad Men. I also like that it has a USB port in the back - bonus functionality point there. I do wish the shade could bend a tiny bit more down to control the brightness better, but I contacted their customer service people about bulb options who quickly responded with suggested models of softer lightbulbs that would work which I'll try out. But I thought it was a great product for a low price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 16, 2019
reviews.reviewText: This is a super sleek looking lamp in person. Right size for a small to average student desk. It has a usb port though I'm not sure my daughter has used that feature so I have no idea how fast or slow the juice goes through it. At any rate, nice looking. Doesn't feel or look cheap. I'd expect to find something of this quality at target, to put it in perspective. The on off switch is on the base instead of the cord which is nice too. Overall we're happy with it!
